<h2>How to Batch-Create a Month of Content</h2>
<p>Veterinary staff are busy. Between appointments, surgeries, and emergencies, social media falls to the bottom of the priority list. The fix: batch creation. One dedicated session per month replaces daily scrambling.</p>
<h3>The 2-Hour Monthly System</h3>
<p><strong>Week 1-4 (during work hours):</strong> Capture content as you go.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Take 2 to 3 patient photos per day (with consent)</li>
<li>[ ] Film 1 short video per week (15 to 30 seconds)</li>
<li>[ ] Save 2 positive reviews per week (screenshots)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Monthly batch session (2 hours):</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Sort photos</strong> into categories: patients, team, educational, seasonal (15 min)</li>
<li><strong>Write captions</strong> for each post. Keep them short. 1 to 3 sentences. (30 min)</li>
<li><strong>Create 4 to 5 educational carousels</strong> in Canva using templates (30 min)</li>
<li><strong>Schedule everything</strong> using Meta Business Suite (free) or Buffer (15 min)</li>
<li><strong>Plan next month's themes</strong> around pet health awareness dates (15 min)</li>
</ol>
